content:
Create Embedded Static Resources

You can create and upload JavaScript files to Salesforce as static resources. These resources can be applied to your website or Experience Builder site.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Setup node is available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Performance, Professional, Unlimited, and Essentials Editions


USER PERMISSIONS
NEEDED
To create and edit static resources: Customize Application AND Author Apex

The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026. Migrate to Messaging for In-App and Web before that date.

Create your JavaScript static resource files, including strings, arrays, JSON, and JS functions. Here are some examples:

Channel Menu Static Resources
Experience Site Static Resources

Then upload JavaScript files to reference in your Channel Menu Experience site or Channel Menu external website deployment. Add files for Embedded Chat to Experience sites only (not available for website pages).

From Setup, enter Static Resources, then select Static Resources.
Click New.
Enter a unique name with no spaces and start with a letter.
Specify an optional description of the resource.
Set the Cache Control to Public.

To apply the resources, return to your code settings in Channel Menu or Experience sites. 

Create JavaScript files to upload as a static resource and apply to Embedded Chat for your Experience Cloud site. Hereâ€™s a code example for chat invitations to get you started.
